2021/12/15 written by Chuo-Yu Yang

Description
(1) char_pipe.c : A char pipe device implemented using kernel memory, device data is designed as a circular queue, the device driver performs blocking I/O and poll operations.
                  A module_param is specified for allocating an ammount of char_pipe device.
(2) usr_pipe.c : A user program that accesses the char_pipe device and performs blocking read/write and polling operations.
